## 1. Setting Up the React Project

### Install Node.js and npm

```shell
apt install nodejs npm -y 
```

### To verify installation use command

```shell
node -v
npm -v
```
## 2. Clone the repository 

```shell
git clone  https://github.com/your-username/your-frontend-repo.git
```
## 3. Install Dependencies

``shell 
npm install
# or
yarn install
```
## 4. Environment Variables

```shell 
Create a .env file in the root directory of the project. The environment file is used to configure runtime variables such as API endpoints, authentication keys, and environment modes.
nano env 
nano dockerfile
FROM node:25-alpine3.21
COPY . /opt
WORKDIR /opt
RUN apk update 
RUN apk add apache2
RUN npm install
RUN npm run build
RUN cp -rf dist/* /var/www/localhost/htdocs/
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["httpd", "-D", "FOREGROUND"]

vim .env 

    VITE_API_URL = "http://<BACKEND_PUBLIC_IP>:8080/api"
```To build the React application for production, run:
npm run build
```

